{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 19:33:52.536102", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nOverview\n- Topology: Spine–leaf SDN with OVS switches (leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1) and hosts (host_1_1, host_1_2, host_2_1, host_2_2). All switches managed by an OpenFlow controller at 20.0.0.100.\n- Objective: Assess current network health, detect anomalies, localize faulty elements, and identify the likely root cause. No remediation is included.\n\nKey Symptoms and Tests\n1) End-host reachability within and across leaves:\n- host_1_1 → host_1_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- host_2_1 → host_2_2: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\n- host_1_1 ↔ host_2_1: 100% loss, “Destination Host Unreachable.”\nInterpretation: Even same-subnet peers on the same leaf cannot communicate.\n\n2) ARP on hosts:\n- ip neigh on hosts shows entries marked “FAILED” for peers (no ARP resolution).\nInterpretation: L2 forwarding/learning is not functioning; ARP requests are not being delivered.\n\n3) OVS controller status on switches:\n- leaf_1, leaf_2, spine_1: fail_mode: secure\n- ovs-vsctl list Controller shows is_connected: false with status last_error=\"Connection refused\", state=BACKOFF to tcp:20.0.0.100:6633.\n- ovs-ofctl dump-flows on all switches returns empty (no flows).\nInterpretation: All switches are disconnected from the controller, and in secure mode drop all traffic when controller is down, leaving no dataplane learning or forwarding.\n\n4) Management network reachability:\n- All switches can ping the controller IP 20.0.0.100 successfully (ICMP OK).\nInterpretation: L3 connectivity to the controller host is fine; the refusal is at the TCP application port level (6633), not a reachability problem in the management network.\n\n5) Interface state/counters:\n- Switch ports to hosts and inter-switch links are UP.\n- Leaf ports RX some frames (e.g., ARP), but TX is 0, consistent with dropping in secure mode due to lack of controller flows.\n\nAnomaly Detection\n- Severe network outage for data-plane traffic: complete loss of host-to-host connectivity and ARP failure.\n- All OVS instances report controller connection refused and have empty flow tables while configured in fail_mode=secure.\n\nFault Localization\n- Not a physical/link issue: interfaces are UP and management network works.\n- Not a host configuration issue: hosts have valid IPs in the same /24 and attempt ARP.\n- Fault lies at the SDN control plane boundary:\n  - The OpenFlow controller endpoint 20.0.0.100:6633 is refusing TCP connections.\n  - All switches are in secure mode and therefore drop traffic without controller-programmed flows.\n\nRoot Cause (Most Likely)\n- The OpenFlow controller service at 20.0.0.100 is not accepting connections on TCP port 6633 (service not running, not listening on 6633, or actively refusing). As a result, all OVS switches are disconnected and, due to fail_mode=secure, are dropping all dataplane traffic. This directly explains the lack of ARP resolution and host communication failures.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 16393, "output_tokens": 1937, "total_tokens": 18330, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 14976}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 1216}}}
